cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about developing end-to-end neural network architectures for Vietnamese named entity recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also extensively studies the use of deep learning models for Vietnamese NER, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses pre-trained word embeddings as input, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the system on a standard test set, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
